INSERT INTO `jobs` VALUES (1,'1st Line Support Analyst','£40k to £60k','1st Line Support Analyst&#xD;<br />&#xD;<br />We are looking for a personable and outgoing 1st Line Support Analyst on a temporary basis  working for an organisation based in Darlington.  Yo will be part of a small team and assist with general day to day support.&#xD;<br />&#xD;<br />You will enjoy speaking to people and be able to build rapport. Provide help with 1st line queries such as password resets, general desktop issues, Internet explorer and connectivity.  Support the existing team fielding calls and engaging with customers.&#xD;<br />&#xD;<br />Calls are higher than normal due to some project implementations so the service desk is a busy environment, you will support around 3,000 users nationally.&#xD;<br />&#xD;<br />You must be immediately available and flexible to start week commencing 15th June 2015.&#xD;<br />',1,'ASAP','1','2017-02-19 12:48:30','2015-06-12 14:02:32','lucy.turner.36547.781@harveynashcareers.com','295950/001','Darlington',NULL,3,115,2,4,1,235,1,NULL),(3,'Procurement Manager ','£40k to £60k','Interim IT Procurement Manager/Programme Manager- &#xD;<br />&#xD;<br />My client is looking for a commercially aware consultant who has come from a Procurement/ Programme Manager to help with the organisations Global Transformation projects. I am therefore looking to speak to individuals who get stuck in/go get attitude but also have some relevant experience and skills and they should include some or all of the following:&#xD;<br />&#xD;<br />*Commercial Acumen&#xD;<br />*Worked in Global organisations&#xD;<br />*Procurement/Purchasing experience spanning 3 years plus experience&#xD;<br />*Change Management experience&#xD;<br />*IT procurement  experience or relevant complex commodity experience... Desirable would be telecoms and software experience in particular.&#xD;<br />*Knowledge of SAP or comparable ERP systems&#xD;<br />*Project Management/Programme Management experience&#xD;<br />*CIPS/MCIPS qualification&#xD;<br />*Six Sigma or equivalent.&#xD;<br />*Demonstrable benefits delivery both quantitative and qualitative&#xD;<br />         Stakeholder engagement and communications skills&#xD;<br />*Degree or relevant work experience.&#xD;<br /> &#xD;<br />&#xD;<br />The role will span the full lifecycle of the organisations transformation projects - preferably from initiation to delivery to the business, this means it could be an 18 months + contract &#xD;<br />&#xD;<br />These roles are pivotal roles so would need a level of seniority and gravitas.&#xD;<br />&#xD;<br />If the role sounds of interests then please submit copy of your CV. &#xD;<br />&#xD;<br />****Successful candidates will be contacted and if you have any questions please send an email********&#xD;<br />',1,'ASAP','3','2017-02-19 12:48:30','2015-06-18 09:07:11','emma.gardiner.31889.781@harveynashcareers.com','295908/004','Coventry',NULL,3,78,2,4,1,235,1,NULL),(4,'SAP APO consultant - SNP','£60000 - £75000 per annum + Benefits','SAP APO consultant - (Advanced Planning and Optimization)&#xD;<br />&#xD;<br />A leading end-user organisation is currently looking for an experienced Senior SAP APO consultant with strong configuration skills to join their in-house SAP team. &#xD;<br />&#xD;<br />You will act as an expert in advising, implementing and supporting best practice solutions in SAP&#x2019;s Supply Chain Management technologies. &#xD;<br />&#xD;<br />Along with this, you will design, develop and implement solutions in conjunction with the project team and lead and own the design of APO solutions.&#xD;<br />&#xD;<br />Other responsibilities:&#xD;<br />*Collection and analysis of user requirements &#xD;<br />*Recommend best practice processes and design, configure and deploy solutions to support them&#xD;<br />*Perform system testing including UAT&#xD;<br />*Prepare documentation and &#xD;<br />*Undertake training workshops (user and super user workshops)&#xD;<br />*Undertake end user training, coaching and support&#xD;<br />*Development and review of functional and technical specifications&#xD;<br />&#xD;<br />Essential Key Skills:&#xD;<br />*Extensive hands-on SAP APO experience&#xD;<br />*Multiple full lifecycle SAP project experience&#xD;<br />*Ideally experience with at least one SNP Planning Engine - Heuristic / CTM / Optimizer&#xD;<br />*Strong configuration skills &#xD;<br />*In-depth knowledge of supply chain processes and best practice&#xD;<br />*Excellent customer facing presentation and communication skills&#xD;<br />&#xD;<br />Desirable skills:&#xD;<br />*Working knowledge of all SCM disciplines&#xD;<br />*Set-Up and management of the Core Interface&#xD;<br />*Knowledge of CIF user exits&#xD;<br />*Working knowledge of B/W&#xD;<br />&#xD;<br />Apply now to avoid disappointment!&#xD;<br />',1,'ASAP','4','2017-02-19 12:48:30','2015-06-19 10:12:39','tom.stroud.86011.781@harveynashcareers.com','283086/005','East Riding of Yorkshire',NULL,5,159,3,4,1,235,1,NULL),(5,'SAP PP consultant - Production Planning','ï¿½50000 - ï¿½60000 per annum + Benefits','SAP PP consultant - Production Planning&#xD;<br />&#xD;<br />We are looking for a SAP PP consultant to help configure the PP module of SAP and deliver business process design or support required change. &#xD;<br />&#xD;<br />You will be working for a leading business in their field and participate in business process design with the Senior SAP PP Analyst and/or SAP PP team lead. &#xD;<br />&#xD;<br />Along with PP configuration and process design, you will work on both projects and business support.&#xD;<br />&#xD;<br />Essential key skills:&#xD;<br />*&#x9;SAP PP Configuration experience&#xD;<br />*&#x9;Knowledge of PP processes&#xD;<br />*&#x9;Master Data&#xD;<br />*&#x9;Experience of interfaces, barcode systems, ALE/Idoc and ABAP debugging (bonus)&#xD;<br />*&#x9;Production issue resolution/support experience &#xD;<br />*&#x9;Working knowledge of SAP APO is desirable&#xD;<br />&#xD;<br />Apply now to avoid disappointment!&#xD;<br />',1,'ASAP','5','2017-02-19 12:48:30','2016-06-08 15:20:40','tom.stroud.41053.781@harveynashcareers.com','288323/007','East Riding of Yorkshire',NULL,4,159,4,4,1,235,1,NULL),(6,'Java Developer ','£40k to £60k','My client is currently looking for a Java Developer to join them on a permanent basis to be based out of their offices in Darlington, working within a large scale ICT Department using various technical platforms and methodologies&#xD;<br />&#xD;<br />Your role will be to provide technical analysis and design solutions in an Oracle/J2EE environment Whilst producing robust, efficient, reliable code and undertake unit testing to the highest standard; Troubleshoot and resolve problems in development, test, training and live environments; Develop software to provide business solutions from functional specifications; Develop and manage the impact of new functionality from work assessments and change requests; &#xD;<br />&#xD;<br />To be successful in this role the ideal candidate will have a proven track record in developing with Java/ J2EE and be able to demonstrate skills in the following areas:&#xD;<br />&#xD;<br />· Good Knowledge of Servlets, EJB or JSF &#xD;<br />· Knowledge of testing frameworks and producing test scripts is essential. &#xD;<br />· You will be comfortable with XML, Spring, Hibernate, Struts (MVC Framework);&#xD;<br />· You will also have working knowledge of JDeveloper or Eclipse IDE, Maven Build scripts, ANT build tool;&#xD;<br />· Working knowledge of RDBMS &#xD;<br />&#xD;<br />You will have a passion for communication and enjoy working in a flexible, laid back environment where people take responsibility for their own workload. If this sounds like a role you can sink your teeth in to then, send your most up to date CV to Aubrey.mazinyi@harveynash.com&#xD;<br />',1,'ASAP','6','2017-02-19 12:48:30','2015-06-19 12:25:19','aubrey.mazinyi.60628.781@harveynashcareers.com','291522/002','Darlington',NULL,5,329,9,4,1,235,1,NULL),(7,'Software Engineer - Multiple Opportunities','Excellent salary and Benefits Package','Harvey Nash&#x2019;s Darlington based client is currently recruiting for talented Java professionals to join a highly-respected public sector organisation. This is an exciting time to join the team as they embark on a transformation project with the aim of updating and modernising their existing systems. Based in a state of the art development centre this is an excellent opportunity for you to join the company at a key stage in their growth.&#xD;<br />&#xD;<br />The Opportunity&#xD;<br />&#xD;<br />You will help to speed up the clients&#x2019; site and deliver new features. You must be motivated and productive with experience in building robust, tested high-volume web applications. It is a great opportunity to work with cutting edge technologies and be part of major projects that will be highly visible. &#xD;<br />&#xD;<br />To apply for this position it is essential that you can demonstrate exposure to, or knowledge of:&#xD;<br />&#xD;<br />A solid Java development background working with Core Java and Enterprise Edition.&#xD;<br />Building scalable, concurrent, high availability systems.&#xD;<br />Creating and interacting relational databases.&#xD;<br />Experience of a continuous deployment environment, with source control and managed releases.&#xD;<br />Ability to work in a highly-collaborative Agile team.&#xD;<br />&#xD;<br />Ultimately you will be joining an organisation that will challenge you to be the best in your field and provide you with a platform to further progress your career. In return for your hard work you will be rewarded in the form of a competitive salary (depending on experience) and a generous benefits package. &#xD;<br />&#xD;<br />To apply send your CV to Nick.gillen@harveynash.com or give us a call on 0131 460 4315 for a confidential chat.&#xD;<br />&#xD;<br />',1,'ASAP','7','2017-02-19 12:48:30','2015-06-19 14:24:27','nick.gillen.42848.781@harveynashcareers.com','290818/012','Darlington',NULL,5,195,2,4,1,235,1,NULL),(8,'Head of Learning Strategy','£55000 - £60000 per annum + car + bonus','In this newly created role Learning & Skills Strategy role you will be given an exciting opportunity to work on a Greenfield project to define, design and implement a new strategic training plan. Reporting directly into the business and as part of the Global Delivery team, your key to success will be your ability to develop effective senior stakeholder relationships and business partner across a global, matrix structure. Working in conjunction with L&D colleagues in Group central functions your will maximise resources and provide leadership locally on all Development activity to include, soft skills, induction, technical and product training.&#xD;<br />&#xD;<br /> &#xD;<br />&#xD;<br />Key Responsibilities&#xD;<br />&#xD;<br /> * &#xD;<br />&#xD;<br />Review current practices and relationships within the business and acting as a consultant, develop new strategies and ways of working that deliver upon business objectives&#xD;<br /> * &#xD;<br />&#xD;<br />Lead, coach and motivate the training team in order to effective deliver upon Global and local strategies&#xD;<br /> * &#xD;<br />&#xD;<br />Act as a champion for learning and skills development and imbed new ways of working&#xD;<br /> * &#xD;<br />&#xD;<br />Develop, implement and approach a blended learning approach&#xD;<br /> * &#xD;<br />&#xD;<br />Network effectively across a complex, global structure to ensure that strategies are fit for purpose at both Global and local levels&#xD;<br /> * &#xD;<br />&#xD;<br />Act as a change agent and innovator to promote a culture of high performance and continuous improvement&#xD;<br />&#xD;<br /> &#xD;<br />&#xD;<br /> &#xD;<br />&#xD;<br />Key Requirements&#xD;<br />&#xD;<br /> * &#xD;<br />&#xD;<br />Experience of working in a similar strategic role within a Global, matrix structure &#xD;<br /> * &#xD;<br />&#xD;<br />Demonstrable experience of working within client focussed, commercial organisations &#xD;<br /> * &#xD;<br />&#xD;<br />Training and Development background &#xD;<br /> * &#xD;<br />&#xD;<br />Experience of designing and implementing new strategies is essential&#xD;<br /> * &#xD;<br />&#xD;<br />Business Partner approach with the ability to build strong relationships and tailor style to different audiences and cultures&#xD;<br /> * &#xD;<br />&#xD;<br />Experience of designing training programmes that are qualification driven is highly beneficial&#xD;<br />&#xD;<br /> &#xD;<br />&#xD;<br /> &#xD;<br />&#xD;<br />About Harvey Nash HR &#xD;<br />&#xD;<br /> We are Harvey Nash HR, specialists in finding and attracting the brightest HR talent to your business. We are part of Harvey Nash, a global professional recruitment consultancy and IT outsourcing service provider. We operate from 40 offices covering the USA, Europe and Asia. &#xD;<br />&#xD;<br /> We recruit HR generalists and specialists from entry-level to the Board, on a permanent, contract and interim basis. More than any other HR recruiter, we actively invest in our community through our established HR surveys, market intelligence and networking events. And being part of the Harvey Nash family allows us to introduce our HR community to a wealth of subject matter experts and wider industry knowledge.&#xD;<br />',1,'ASAP','8','2017-02-19 12:48:30','2015-06-19 15:27:09','abby.savage.91695.781@harveynashcareers.com','296152/001','North West',NULL,5,229,5,4,1,235,1,NULL),(9,'Senior SAP Infrastructure Project Manager','£45000 - £55000 per annum + Benefits','Senior SAP Infrastructure Project Manager - Basis, NetWeaver&#xD;<br />&#xD;<br />Harvey Nash is looking for a skilled SAP Infrastructure Project Manager to join a global blue-chip organisation.&#xD;<br />&#xD;<br />You will work as part of the SAP Infrastructure CoE in alignment with the organisations goals.  You will take responsibility for the definition, documentation and safe execution of projects as well as actively participating in all phases of the project.&#xD;<br />&#xD;<br />Other key responsibilities:&#xD;<br />*&#x9;Identify, assess and manage risks to the success of the project&#xD;<br />*&#x9;Ensures that realistic project and quality plans are prepared and maintained &#xD;<br />*&#x9;Monitors costs, timescales and resources used, and take action where these deviate from agreed tolerances&#xD;<br />*&#x9;Ensures that delivered systems are implemented within specified criteria&#xD;<br />*&#x9;Initiates and influences relationships with and between key stakeholders&#xD;<br />*&#x9;Provides effective leadership to the project team ensuring that team members are motivated and developing their skills and experience&#xD;<br />*&#x9;Determine the readiness levels of business users with regard to upcoming changes; uncovers readiness gaps and create and implement action plans to close the gaps prior to go-live&#xD;<br />&#xD;<br />Essential key skills:&#xD;<br />*&#x9;Broad understanding of SAP Basis in Global Environment&#xD;<br />*&#x9;Broad knowledge of Global SAP infrastructure (inc. storage, network, servers, tooling, capacity management & planning)&#xD;<br />*&#x9;Broad knowledge of SAP Landscape management (System refreshes and release cycles)&#xD;<br />*&#x9;Experience of system migrations, EHP upgrades, AIX patching & Db2 upgrade&#xD;<br />*&#x9;Experience with business case preparation, project definition, planning, risk management, project change control, configuration management, financial management and staff selection for managing projects&#xD;<br />*&#x9;Project management methodologies. Example: PRINCE2 / PMI&#xD;<br />*&#x9;Service Management &#xD;<br />*&#x9;Methods and techniques for reporting progress and financial compliance against an agreed plan&#xD;<br />*&#x9;Methods, techniques associated with Global change control&#xD;<br />&#xD;<br />Apply now to avoid disappointment!&#xD;<br />',1,'ASAP','9','2017-02-19 12:48:30','2015-06-19 10:32:51','tom.stroud.01539.781@harveynashcareers.com','291405/002','Merseyside',NULL,5,159,10,4,1,235,1,NULL),(10,'Incident and Problem Manager','&#x20AC;25000 - &#x20AC;30000 per annum','Problem and Incident Manager&#xD;<br />&#xD;<br />Manchester&#xD;<br />&#xD;<br />Up to £350 p/day&#xD;<br />&#xD;<br />3-6 months&#xD;<br />&#xD;<br />My client who are a well known ecommerce business are in need of a Problem and Incident Manager. They do operate in an ITIL environment and so ITIL experience is needed however the client are quite a fast paced and agile environment so they need someone who is used to not always following guidelines.&#xD;<br />&#xD;<br />An Incident Manager has responsibility for: &#xD;<br />&#xD;<br /> * Driving the efficiency and effectiveness of the incident management process in an ecommerce environment&#xD;<br /> * Collaborating with development and service teams&#xD;<br /> * Producing management information, including KPIs and reports &#xD;<br /> * Monitoring the effectiveness of incident management and making recommendations for improvement &#xD;<br /> * Developing and maintaining the incident management system &#xD;<br /> * Driving, developing, managing and maintaining the major incident process and associated procedures &#xD;<br /> * Reviewing and auditing the process &#xD;<br /> * Ensuring that all IT development and support teams follow the incident management process for every incident &#xD;<br />&#xD;<br />Experience needed:&#xD;<br />&#xD;<br />5+ years Problem and Incident Management experience&#xD;<br />eCommerce or online experience&#xD;<br />ITIL and some Agile&#xD;<br />exposure to collaborating/managing incidents from App/Development and Service teams.&#xD;<br />',1,'ASAP','10','2017-02-19 12:48:30','2015-06-15 17:03:45','mike.gittins.62899.781@harveynashcareers.com','295999/001','Manchester',NULL,3,120,2,4,1,235,1,NULL),(11,'PMO Analyst - £325pd','£300 - £325 per day','PMO Analyst - West Yorkshire at £325pd on initial 3 months contract&#xD;<br />&#xD;<br />My prestigious client in West Yorkshire is looking for a PMO Analyst on initial 3 months contract at £325 per day.&#xD;<br />&#xD;<br />Your core responsibilities will be to facilitate the smooth running of the programme and make sure that governance processes are adhered to. This will be done through weekly reporting and dashboards, supporting project meetings, managing the change request process. &#xD;<br />&#xD;<br />ideally looking for candidates with the following skills:&#xD;<br />&#xD;<br />* Track record of working in a project management office (PMO) &#xD;<br />* Experience of working on large technology (IT) and business change projects &#xD;<br />* Thorough knowledge of project management processes, standards and practices &#xD;<br />* Excellent stakeholder management skills &#xD;<br />* Any experience of working within the financial services industry is highly advantageous &#xD;<br />&#xD;<br />It is based in West Yorkshire; just north of Bradford and paying between £300 to £325 per day depending on experience.&#xD;<br />&#xD;<br />Please send your CV for immediate, confidential discussion&#xD;<br />',0,'ASAP','11','2017-02-19 12:48:30','2015-06-15 12:09:44','kirill.pozdnjakov.81000.781@harveynashcareers.com','289026/004','West Yorkshire',NULL,3,230,5,4,1,235,1,NULL),(12,' UAT / Packaging Tech Lead - Application Packaging - Leeds ','£300 - £340 per day','UAT Tech Lead required by my energy client in Leeds.&#xD;<br />&#xD;<br />The successful UAT Tech Lead will drive the UAT testing process of a major Application Packaging and Discovery Project for a leading energy company.&#xD;<br />&#xD;<br />In order to be successful the UAT Tech Lead should have proven experience of leading the UAT testing element of a similar project in a large enterprise environment. You should be client facing and a strong communicator.&#xD;<br />&#xD;<br />This is an urgent requirement so p