M (CORM) department is responsible for the development and maintenance of the global framework for assessing and managing compliance and operational risk in the company. The CORM department provides compliance and ORM subject matter expertise to the Group CRO through input for and review of policies, practices, methodologies, business initiatives and reporting. Next to that the department supports local businesses in implementing the global framework and provides expertise where needed. The department also monitors the compliance and operational risk exposures at group level and compliance with group specific portions of compliance and operational risk policies. The department works with the Reporting Team on receiving appropriate reporting regarding compliance and operational risks for use in the Global Risk & Capital Committee (GRCC), Management Board and Supervisory Board.&#xD;<br />&#xD;<br /> &#xD;<br />&#xD;<br />Job description&#xD;<br />&#xD;<br />The CORM Department of Group Risk, seeks a highly professional Interim Risk Manager. The Risk Manager will be responsible for managing a broad range of assignments within CORM involving SOx program activities, scenario analysis, risk control self-assessment, risk reporting and monitoring, etc.&#xD;<br />&#xD;<br /> &#xD;<br />&#xD;<br />Responsibilities will involve:&#xD;<br />&#xD;<br />Support maintenance of ORM risk control activities, potentially including:&#xD;<br />&#xD;<br /> &#xD;<br />&#xD;<br />SOx 404 Methodology / Global program: Support in preparation of agenda for monthly global SOx meeting, Support in expanding Group SOx oversight and challenge role for the business units(collect and document global list of SOx controls, applications and control deficiencies, monitoring of remediation plans), Support in conducting country unit SOx program assessment, support in maintenance of SOx 404 Methodology. Support on preparation and implementation of the SOx Global program.&#xD;<br />&#xD;<br /> &#xD;<br />&#x